<strong>Memory Detection</strong>

Case ID: mem-001

Using Unity
<dl>
    <dt>Press the Super (Windows) Key or click on the Ubuntu logo on the Unity panel then search for and open System Monitor</dt>
        <dd>System monitor should open</dd>
        <dd>System monitor should detect the correct amount of memory</dd>
</dl>

<strong>Open Applications</strong>

Case ID: mem-002

Using Unity
<dl>
    <dt>Once your desktop is installed, open around 10 applications.</dt> 
    <dt>Click on Ubuntu Logo and search Terminal.</dt> 
    <dt>Type "top" and press Enter.</dt> 
    <dt>Leave this to run for a while to check for memory leaks.</dt> 
        <dd>Memory usage should remain relatively stable when no additional applications are opened</dd>
</dl>

